@daisy-ycguo it appears this file has existed in the public domain for some time.  For example, this file also exists in other projects such as:
[https://github.com/wala/WALA/blob/master/com.ibm.wala.util/src/com/ibm/wala/util/collections/Pair.java](https://github.com/wala/WALA/blob/master/com.ibm.wala.util/src/com/ibm/wala/util/collections/Pair.java)


We cannot remove the original license header; in fact we need to note it as an exception and likely remove the ASF header.

@csantanapr Many VM services provide option to enable VM protection.
If user enables that option, no one can delete that VM until user explicitly disables protection.

So I naively thought that if user can enable protection against actions, user can protect important(used in production) actions from accidental deletion.
